The Celtics improve to 21-21 on the season, while the Magic fall to 14-28.

In his Nets debut, Blake Griffin recorded two points (1-2 FG), two rebounds and one block as they defeated the Wizards, 113-106. Kyrie Irving (28 points, seven rebounds, six assists) and James Harden (26 points, five rebounds, eight assists) combined for 54 points for the Nets in the victory. Russell Westbrook recorded 29 points, 13 rebounds and 13 assists for the Wizards in the losing effort, his 14th triple-double of the season and 160th of his career. The Nets improve to 29-14 on the season, while the Wizards fall to 15-26.

The Bulls defeated the Pistons, 100-86. Zach LaVine led the Bulls with 18 points, while Lauri Markkanen added 16 points and eight rebounds in the victory. Jerami Grant led the way for the Pistons with a game-high 26 points in the losing effort. The Bulls improve to 19-22 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 12-30.

Led by Collin Sextons 36 points and four assists, the Cavaliers defeated the Raptors, 116-105. Additionally for the Cavaliers, Jarrett Allen added 17 points and 15 rebounds in the victory, while Fred VanVleet tallied 23 points and seven assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Cavaliers improve to 16-26 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 17-25.

Tobias Harris made two free throws with 5.3 seconds remaining in overtime to lift the 76ers over the Knicks, 101-100. Harris finished the game with 20 points, four rebounds and four assists, while Ben Simmons added 16 points and eight rebounds in the victory. Julius Randle recorded 24 points, seven rebounds and a career-high five steals for the Knicks in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 30-13 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 21-22.

Luka Doncic recorded 37 points, including a career-high tying eight 3pt FGM for the Mavericks as they defeated the Trail Blazers, 132-92. Kristaps Porzingis added 12 points and eight rebounds for the Mavericks in the victory, while Damian Lillard tallied 19 points and four assists for the Trail Blazers in the losing effort. The Mavericks improve to 22-19 on the season, while the Trail Blazers fall to 25-17.

The Nets lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Sunday, May 30 at 7:00 p.m. ET
Kawhi Leonard and Paul George combine for 65 on 24-for-35 shooting as the Clippers overcome a 19-point deficit in a game they had to win.

Led by Giannis Antetokounmpos 20 points, 12 rebounds and Playoff career-high 15 assists, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 6 seed Heat, 120-103, in Game 4. Brook Lopez added a game-high 25 points (11-15 FG) for the Bucks in the victory, while Jimmy Butler tallied 12 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for the Heat in the losing effort. The Bucks have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-0, and will advance to the Eastern Conference Semifinals to face the winner of the Brooklyn Nets  Boston Celtics series (Brooklyn currently leads, 2-1).
Led by Norman Powell's 29 points, Portland cruises to a Game 4 victory over Denver and pulls even in the series.
Items.vs: Portland Trail Blazers vs. Denver Nuggets

Items.description: Kia MVP finalist Joel Embiid sets a career playoff high with 36 points, and the 76ers rout the Wizards to take a commanding 3-0 series lead.

After closing the game on a 14-2 run, the No. 1 seed Jazz defeated the No. 8 seed Grizzlies, 121-111, in Game 3. Donovan Mitchell led the way for the Jazz with 29 points (10 in the 4th quarter) and five assists, while Mike Conley added 27 points (7-10 3pt FG), six rebounds and eight assists in the victory. Ja Morant tallied a team-high 28 points and seven assists for the Grizzlies in the losing effort. The Jazz lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Monday, May 31 at 9:30 p.m. ET

Led by Trae Youngs 27 points and nine assists, the No. 5 seed Hawks defeated the No. 4 seed Knicks, 113-96, in Game 4. Additionally for the Hawks, John Collins recorded 22 points and eight rebounds in the victory, while Julius Randle tallied 23 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Hawks lead this best-of-seven series, 3-1, with Game 5 taking place on Wednesday, June 2 at 7:30 p.m. ET
Items.vs: Atlanta Hawks vs. New York Knicks

Items.description: Led by Chris Pauls 18 points and nine assists, the No. 2 seed Suns defeated the No. 7 seed Lakers, 100-92, in Game 4. Devin Booker (17 points, seven rebounds, five assists) and Deandre Ayton (14 points, 17 rebounds) combined for 31 points for the Suns in the victory, while LeBron James tallied 25 points, 12 rebounds and six assists for the Lakers in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 2-2, with Game 5 taking place on Tuesday, June 1 at 10:00 p.m. ET.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Phoenix Suns

Items.description: Kevin Durant (42 points, 14-20 FG), Kyrie Irving (39 points, 11 rebounds) and James Harden (23 points, five rebounds, Playoff career-high 18 assists) combined for 104 points for the No. 2 seed Nets as they defeated the No. 7 seed Celtics, 141-126, in Game 4. Jayson Tatum tallied 40 points, seven rebounds and five assists for the Celtics in the losing effort. The Nets lead this best-of-seven series, 3-1, with Game 5 taking place on Tuesday, June 1

Kawhi Leonard recorded 29 points (11-15 FG) and 10 rebounds for the No. 4 seed Clippers as they defeated the No. 5 seed Mavericks, 106-81, in Game 4. Paul George added 20 points and nine rebounds for the Clippers in the victory, while Luka Doncic tallied 19 points, six rebounds and six assists for the Mavericks in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 2-2, with Game 5 taking place on Wednesday, June 2 at 10:00 p.m. ET.

Led by Russell Westbrooks 19 points, 14 assists and Playoff career-high 21 rebounds, the No. 8 seed Wizards defeated the No. 1 seed 76ers, 122-114, in Game 4. Bradley Beal added a game-high 27 points for the Wizards in the victory, while Tobias Harris tallied 21 points, 13 rebounds and five assists for the 76ers in the losing effort. The 76ers lead this best-of-seven series, 3-1, with Game 5 taking place on Wednesday, June 2 at 7:00 p.m. ET
Donovan Mitchell leads all scorers with 30 points, and Utah uses another composed finish to earn three closeout opportunities against Memphis.
Brooklyn's superstar trio of Kevin Durant, James Harden and Kyrie Irving combine for 83 points in the clincher.
Despite Damian Lillard's record-setting night, Noikola Jokic and Denver walk away with a 2OT win and a 3-2 series lead.
Items.vs: Denver Nuggets vs. Portland Trail Blazers

Items.description: Devin Booker scores 30 points as Phoenix takes full advantage of Anthony Davis' absence and sends LeBron James to the locker room early.
Items.vs: Phoenix Suns vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: Led by Ben Simmons 19 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists, the No. 1 seed 76ers defeated the No. 8 seed Wizards, 129-112, in Game 5. Seth Curry (Playoff career-high 30 points) and Tobias Harris (28 points, nine rebounds, six assists) added 58 points for the 76ers in the victory, while Bradley Beal led all scorers with 32 points, seven rebounds and five assists for the Wizards in the losing effort. The 76ers have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-1, and will advance to the Eastern Conference Semifinals to face the winner of the New York Knicks  Atlanta Hawks series (Atlanta currently leads, 3-1).
Trae Young scores 18 of his 36 points in the 4th quarter as the Hawks ended the Knicks' return to the playoffs in the 1st round.
Items.vs: New York Knicks vs. Atlanta Hawks

Items.description: Led by Donovan Mitchells 30 points, six rebounds and 10 assists, the No. 1 seed Jazz defeated the No. 8 seed Grizzlies, 126-110, in Game 5. Rudy Gobert added 23 points (10-13 FG), 15 rebounds and three blocks for the Jazz in the victory, while Ja Morant tallied 27 points, seven rebounds and 11 assists for the Grizzlies in the losing effort. The Jazz have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-1, and will advance to the Western Conference Semifinals to face the winner of the LA Clippers  Dallas Mavericks series (series is currently tied, 2-2).

Led by Luka Doncics 42 points, eight rebounds and Playoff career-high 14 assists, the No. 5 seed Mavericks defeated the No. 4 seed Clippers, 105-100, in Game 5. Paul George recorded 23 points, 10 rebounds, six assists and three blocks for the Clippers in the losing effort. The Mavericks lead this best-of-seven series, 3-2, with Game 6 taking place on Friday, June 4 at 9:00 p.m. ET

After closing the game on a 24-9 run, the No. 3 seed Nuggets defeated the No. 6 seed Trail Blazers, 126-115, in Game 6. Nikola Jokic led the way for the Nuggets with 36 points, eight rebounds and six assists, while Monte Morris added 22 points (16 in the 2nd half) and a Playoff career-high nine assists in the victory. Damian Lillard tallied 28 points, four rebounds and 13 assists for the Trail Blazers in the losing effort. The Nuggets have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-2, and will advance to the Western Conference Semifinals to face the winner of the Phoenix Suns  Los Angeles Lakers series (Phoenix currently leads, 3-2).
Items.vs: Portland Trail Blazers vs. Denver Nuggets

Items.description: Led by Devin Bookers Playoff career-high 47 points (15-22 FG, 8-10 3pt FG) and 11 rebounds, the No. 2 seed Suns defeated the No. 7 seed Lakers, 113-100, in Game 6. Chris Paul added eight points and 12 assists for the Suns in the victory, while LeBron James tallied 29 points, nine rebounds and seven assists for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Suns have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-2, and will advance to the Western Conference Semifinals to face the No. 3 seed Nuggets.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Phoenix Suns

Items.description: Kawhi Leonard recorded a Playoff career-high tying 45 points (18-25 FG), along with six rebounds for the No. 4 seed Clippers as they defeated the No. 5 seed Mavericks, 104-97, in Game 6. Paul George added 20 points, 13 rebounds and six assists for the Clippers in the victory, while Luka Doncic tallied 29 points, eight rebounds and 11 assists for the Mavericks in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 3-3, with Game 7 taking place on Sunday, June 6 at 3:30 p.m. ET.
Propelled by Kyrie Irving and Kevin Durant, Brooklyn holds off Giannis and Milwaukee in the series opener.
Led by Trae Young's 35 points and 10 assists and Bodan Bogdanovic's 21 points, Atlanta races to a massive lead and fends off Philly for the Game 1 win.
Driven by the excellence of Kawhi Leonard and 20 3-pointers, the Clippers advance despite a monster performance from Mavericks star Luka Donicic.
Game 2 is decided almost immediately as Brooklyn, led by Kevin Durant's scorching start, never trails and leads by as many as 49 points.
Chris Paul, Devin Booker, Deandre Ayton and Mikal Bridges all score 20 or more points as the Suns claim the series opener.
Joel Embiid does the heavy lifting (40 and 13) and Shake Milton erupts for 14 points in 14 minutes in the second half to seal the victory.
The Jazz get 45 points from star guard Donovan Mitchell and the Game 1 victory despite missing 20 straight shots in the first half.

Led by Chris Pauls 17 points, 15 assists and zero turnovers, the No. 2 seed Suns defeated the No. 3 seed Nuggets, 123-98, in Game 2. Devin Booker added 18 points and 10 rebounds for the Suns in the victory, while Nikola Jokic led all scorers with 24 points, 13 rebounds and six assists for the Nuggets in the losing effort. The Suns lead this best-of-seven series, 2-0, with Game 3 taking place on Friday, June 11 at 10:00 p.m. ET

Led by Khris Middletons 35 points and Playoff career-high 15 rebounds, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 2 seed Nets, 86-83, in Game 3. Giannis Antetokounmpo added 33 points and 14 rebounds for the Bucks in the victory, while Kevin Durant tallied 30 points (23 in the 2nd half), 11 rebounds, five assists and four steals for the Nets in the losing effort. The Nets lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Sunday, June 13 at 3:00 p.m. ET

Led by Donovan Mitchells 37 points, the No. 1 seed Jazz defeated the No. 4 seed Clippers, 117-111, in Game 2. Rudy Gobert added 13 points, three blocks and a Playoff career-high 20 rebounds for the Jazz in the victory, while Paul George tallied 27 points, 10 rebounds and six assists for the Clippers in the losing effort. The Jazz lead this best-of-seven series, 2-0, with Game 3 taking place on Saturday, June 12
This enthralling series shifts to Atlanta where the Hawks will need to contain Joel Embiid following the big man’s 40-point performance in game two.
The Suns trail for a grand total of 24 seconds, leaving no doubt as they dominate Game 3 to tighten the screws on the Nuggets.

Led by Kawhi Leonards 34 points, 12 rebounds and five assists, the No. 4 seed Clippers defeated the No. 1 seed Jazz, 132-106, in Game 3. Paul George added 31 points (6-10 3pt FG) and five assists for the Clippers in the victory, while Donovan Mitchell tallied 30 points, five rebounds and four assists for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Jazz lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Monday, June 14 at 10:00 p.m. ET.

Led by Giannis Antetokounmpos 34 points and 12 rebounds, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 2 seed Nets, 107-96, in Game 4. Khris Middleton added 19 points and eight assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Kevin Durant tallied 28 points, 13 rebounds and five assists for the Nets in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 2-2.

Chris Paul recorded 37 points (14-19 FG) and seven assists for the No. 2 seed Suns as they defeated the No. 3 seed Nuggets, 125-118, in Game 4. Devin Booker added 34 points and 11 rebounds for the Suns in the victory, while Will Barton tallied 25 points and five rebounds for the Nuggets in the losing effort. The Suns have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-0, and will advance to the Western Conference Finals for the first time since 2010 and will face the winner of the Utah JazzLA Clippers series (Utah currently leads, 2-1).

After trailing by as many as 18 points, the No. 5 seed Hawks defeated the No. 1 seed 76ers, 103-100, in Game 4. Trae Young led the way for the Hawks with 25 points and a Playoff career-high 18 assists, while Joel Embiid tallied 17 points and a Playoff career-high 21 rebounds for the 76ers in the losing effort. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 2-2, with Game 5 taking place on Wednesday, June 16 at 7:30 p.m. ET
Kawhi Leonard and Paul George answer the bell once again as the Clippers lead by as many as 29 to give the Jazz another thrashing.

Led by Kevin Durants 49 points (31 in the 2nd half), 17 rebounds and 10 assists, the No. 2 seed Nets defeated the No. 3 seed Bucks, 114-108, in Game 5. Jeff Green (27 points, 7-8 3pt FG) and James Harden (five points, six rebounds, eight assists) added 32 points for the Nets in the victory, while Giannis Antetokounmpo tallied 34 points, 12 rebounds and four assists for the Bucks in the losing effort. The Nets lead this best-of-seven series, 3-2, with Game 6 taking place on Thursday, June 17 at 8:30 p.m. ET

After trailing by as many as 26 points, the No. 5 seed Hawks defeated the No. 1 seed 76ers, 109-106, in Game 5. Trae Young led the way for the Hawks with a Playoff career-high 39 points, along with seven assists in the victory, while Joel Embiid (37 points, 13 rebounds, five assists, four blocks) and Seth Curry (Playoff career-high 36 points, seven 3pt FGM) combined for 73 points for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Hawks lead this best-of-seven series, 3-2, with Game 6 taking place on Friday, June 18 at 7:30 p.m. ET
Game 5 belongs to Paul George, who becomes the first player in Clippers history to post 35 points, 15 rebounds and 5 assists in a playoff game.
Joel Embiid, Serth Curry and Tobias Harris score more than 20 apiece as the 76ers hold off the Hawks to force the series back to Philadelphia for a Game 7.

After trailing by as many as 25 points, the No. 4 seed Clippers defeated the No. 1 seed Jazz, 131-119, in Game 6. Terance Mann recorded a Playoff career-high 39 points (7-10 3pt FG), while Paul George (28 points, nine rebounds, seven assists) and Reggie Jackson (27 points, 10 assists) combined for 55 points in the victory. Donovan Mitchell tallied 39 points (9-15 3pt FG), along with nine rebounds and nine assists for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Clippers have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-2, and will advance to the Western Conference Finals for the first time in franchise history to face the No. 2 seed Phoenix Suns.

Led by Giannis Antetokounmpos 40 points, 13 rebounds and five assists, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 2 seed Nets in overtime, 115-111, in Game 7. Khris Middleton added 23 points, 10 rebounds, six assists and five steals for the Bucks in the victory, while Kevin Durant tallied 48 points, nine rebounds and six assists for the Nets. The Bucks have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-3, and will advance to the Eastern Conference Finals to face the winner of the Philadelphia 76ersAtlanta Hawks series (series is currently tied, 3-3).

Led by Devin Bookers 40 points, 13 rebounds and 11 assists, the No. 2 seed Suns defeated the No. 4 seed Clippers, 120-114, in Game 1. Deandre Ayton added 20 points and nine rebounds for the Suns in the victory, while Paul George tallied 34 points, four rebounds and five assists for the Clippers. The Suns lead this best-of-seven series, 1-0, with Game 2 taking place on Tuesday, June 22 at 9:00 p.m. ET

Led by Kevin Huerters Playoff career-high 27 points, the No. 5 seed Hawks defeated the No. 1 seed 76ers, 103-96, in Game 7. Trae Young added 21 points (5-23 FG) and 10 assists for the Hawks in the victory, while Joel Embiid led all scorers with 31 points and 11 rebounds for the 76ers. The Hawks have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-3, and will advance to the Eastern Conference Finals to face the No. 3 seed Milwaukee Bucks.
After a game-winning dunk with 0.7 seconds remaining, the Suns now lead this best-of-seven series, 2-0.
Trae Young scores a playoff career-high 48 points while John Collins and Clint Capela add double-doubles to help Atlanta hold off the Bucks in the series opener.

Led by Paul George's 27 points, 15 rebounds and eight assists, the No. 4 seed Clippers defeated the No. 2 seed Suns, 106-92, in Game 3, snapping Phoenix's nine-game win streak. Reggie Jackson added 23 points (10 in the 4th quarter) for the Clippers in the victory, while Chris Paul tallied 15 points and 12 assists for the Suns. The Suns lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Saturday, June 26 at 9:00 p.m. ET

Led by Giannis Antetokounmpos 25 points, nine rebounds and six assists, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 5 seed Hawks, 125-91, in Game 2. Jrue Holiday added 22 points and seven assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Trae Young tallied 15 points and three assists for the Hawks. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 1-1, with Game 3 taking place on Sunday, June 27 at 8:30 p.m. ET
Phoenix survives the lowest-scoring game of the NBA season to move within one win of its first trip to The Finals since 1993.

Khris Middleton recorded 38 points (20 in the 4th quarter), along with 11 rebounds and seven assists for the No. 3 seed Bucks as they defeated the No. 5 seed Hawks, 113-102, in Game 3. Giannis Antetokounmpo added 33 points, 11 rebounds and four assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Trae Young tallied 35 points and four assists for the Hawks. The Bucks lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Tuesday, June 29 at 8:30 p.m. ET.

Led by Paul George's Playoff career-high 41 points (30 points, 10-12 FG in the 2nd half), along with 13 rebounds and six assists, the No. 4 seed Clippers defeated the No. 2 seed Suns, 116-102, in Game 5. Reggie Jackson added 23 points, five rebounds and three assists for the Clippers in the victory, while Devin Booker tallied 31 points, four rebounds and three assists for the Suns. The Suns lead this best-of-seven series, 3-2, with Game 6 taking place on Wednesday, June 30 at 9:00 p.m. ET

Led by Lou Williams 21 points (7-9 FG), five rebounds and eight assists, the No. 5 seed Hawks defeated the No. 3 seed Bucks, 110-88, in Game 4. Bogdan Bogdanovic added 20 points, five assists and four steals for the Hawks in the victory, while Jrue Holiday tallied 19 points and nine assists for the Bucks. This best-of-seven series in now tied, 2-2, with Game 5 taking place on Thursday, July 1 at 8:30 p.m. ET

Led by Chris Pauls Playoff career-high tying 41 points (31 points, 12-16 FG in the 2nd half), along with eight assists, the No. 2 seed Suns defeated the No. 4 seed Clippers, 130-103, in Game 6. Devin Booker added 22 points, seven rebounds and four assists for the Suns in the victory, while Paul George tallied 21 points and nine rebounds for the Clippers. The Suns have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-2, and will advance to the NBA Finals for the third time in franchise history and the first time since 1993 to face the winner of the Atlanta Hawks-Milwaukee Bucks series (series is currently tied, 2-2).

Led by Brook Lopezs Playoff career-high 33 points (14-18 FG), along with seven rebounds and four blocks, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 5 seed Hawks, 123-112, in Game 5. Khris Middleton (26 points, 13 rebounds, eight assists), Jrue Holiday (25 points, 13 assists) and Bobby Portis (Playoff career-high 22 points) helped lift the Bucks to the victory, while Bogdan Bogdanovic tallied 28 points, five rebounds and four assists for the Hawks. The Bucks lead this best-of-seven series, 3-2, with Game 6 taking place on Saturday, July 3

Led by Jrue Holidays 27 points, nine rebounds, nine assists and four steals, the No. 3 seed Bucks defeated the No. 5 seed Hawks, 118-107, in Game 6. Khris Middleton added a game-high 32 points (27 in the 2nd half), along with seven assists and three steals for the Bucks in the victory, while Trae Young tallied 14 points, four rebounds and nine assists for the Hawks. The Bucks have now closed out this best-of-seven series, 4-2, and will advance to the NBA Finals for the third time in franchise history and the first time since 1974 to face the Phoenix Suns. Game 1 of the 2021 NBA Finals will take place on Tuesday, July 6.
Devin Booker and Chris Paul combine for 59 points, Deandre Ayton posts a huge double-double and Phoenix makes an opening statement in Game  1.
Devin Booker scores 31 points and Mikal Bridges adds 27 to help the Suns erase an early deficit and hold off the Bucks late in Game 2.

Led by Giannis Antetokounmpos 41 points (14-23 FG, 13-17 FT), 13 rebounds and six assists, the Bucks defeated the Suns, 120-100, in Game 3. Jrue Holiday added 21 points, five rebounds and nine assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Chris Paul tallied 19 points and nine assists for the Suns. The Suns lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1, with Game 4 taking place on Wednesday, July 14 at 9:00 p.m. ET

Led by Khris Middletons 40 points (24 in the 2nd half), six rebounds and four assists, the Bucks defeated the Suns, 109-103, in Game 4. Giannis Antetokounmpo added 26 points, 14 rebounds and eight assists for the Bucks in the victory, while Devin Booker tallied a game-high 42 points for the Suns. This best-of-seven series is now tied, 2-2, with Game 5 taking place on Saturday, July 17 at 9:00 p.m. ET
Led by Giannis Antetokounmpo's 32 points and Khris Middleton's 29, the Bucks beat the Suns to take a 3-2 lead back to Milwaukee.
Named Finals MVP, Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 50 points with 14 rebounds and 5 blocks in a historic closeout performance.
— Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks didn't let the celebration of the franchise's first NBA championship in half a century distract them as they opened their title defense.
— Opening night in Hollywood went well for three quarters for Los Angeles Lakers superstars LeBron James and Anthony Davis against Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Golden State Warriors

Items.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 31 points, hitting seven 3-pointers, and the Charlotte Hornets used a 24-0 third period run to battle back and beat the Indiana Pacers 123-122 on Wednesday night.
— Zach LaVine can still score in bunches when needed.
— The New York Knicks never could contain Jaylen Brown and on the last play of regulation completely lost track of Marcus Smart.
Items.vs: New York Knicks vs. Boston Celtics

Items.description: — The Washington Wizards have a new coach and a new supporting cast around Bradley Beal, the superstar they are hoping will lead the franchise out of its enduring doldrums.

— Ja Morant had 37 points and six assists, De’Anthony Melton added 20 points and the Memphis Grizzlies pulled away in the fourth for a 132-121 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night in the opener for both teams.

— Joel Embiid and those members of the Philadelphia 76ers who made the trip to New Orleans for their regular-season opener looked unfazed by the absence of Ben Simmons and unaffected by the drama surrounding the disgruntled All-Star guard.

— Anthony Edwards energized the first full-size home crowd of his nascent career with 29 points in 31 minutes for the Minnesota Timberwolves, who cruised to a 124-106 victory over the Houston Rockets to start the season on Wednesday night.
— San Antonio coach Gregg Popovich has loosened things up on the court after years of structure and it resulted in another successful opener for the Spurs.
Items.vs: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic

Items.description: — The Utah Jazz opened a new season with a typical dominant defensive performance.
Items.vs: Utah Jazz vs. Oklahoma City Thunder

Items.description: — The Sacramento Kings will be in a good place this season if Harrison Barnes can consistently shoot like he did in the season opener.
Items.vs: Portland Trail Blazers vs. Sacramento Kings

Items.description: — Nikola Jokic was up to his old tricks Wednesday night, scoring on a crafty array of hook shots, 3-pointers and flat-footed jumpers.
— Beginning a season of high expectations, the Atlanta Hawks showed they're far more than Trae Young.
— Only one thing went wrong for the Miami Heat on Thursday night. Udonis Haslem voted no.
— Stephen Curry raised his arms, waved to acknowledge the adoring fans as shot after shot dropped through the net and screamed in celebration — no trash about it.
Items.vs: Golden State Warriors vs. LA Clippers

Items.description: — Bradley Beal's absence put Spencer Dinwiddie and Kyle Kuzma on the spot — and those two made quite a first impression on their new fans in Washington.
— For the second straight game, the Hornets saved their best for last.

— As Tom Thibodeau headed in for his postgame news conference following the New York Knicks’ 121-96 rout of the Orlando Magic on Friday night, a fan implored the notoriously grumpy head coach to “be happy.”
Items.vs: Orlando Magic vs. New York Knicks

Items.description: — Ben Simmons wasn't there. Joel Embiid conceded he should not have played. With Philadelphia's All-Star cornerstones absent or injured, Kevin Durant and Brooklyn had the opening they needed to spoil the 76ers' opener with a rally down the stretch.
— Raptors coach Nick Nurse didn't think Scottie Barnes played that badly in his first NBA game.
— Christian Wood had 31 points and 14 rebounds and Houston beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 124-91 on Friday night in the Rockets’ home opener.
Items.vs: Houston Rockets vs. Oklahoma City Thunder

Items.description: — Zach LaVine needed some time to get going. Once he did, there was no stopping him.
Items.vs: Chicago Bulls vs. New Orleans Pelicans

Items.description: — Not everyone thought Nikola Jokic should have won the MVP award last season. His Denver teammates did, and one, in fact, predicted he would repeat.
Items.vs: Denver Nuggets vs. San Antonio Spurs

Items.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points, Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 20 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the Sacramento Kings 110-101 on Friday night.
— Dwight Howard and Anthony Davis both say their physical confrontation on the Los Angeles Lakers' bench was a momentary disagreement that has already been resolved.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Phoenix Suns

Items.description: — Rookie Evan Mobley collected 17 points, 11 rebounds and four blocked shots, helping the Cleveland Cavaliers rally for their first win of the season, 101-95 over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
— After not playing much defense in the season's first two games, the Indiana Pacers were far more stingy against the Miami Heat.
— Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks shook off the disappointment of a season-opening defeat with an impressive comeback win in Toronto.
— DeMar DeRozan scored 21 points, Nikola Vucevic added 15 points and 18 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls beat the Detroit Pistons 97-82 on Saturday night.

— Karl-Anthony Towns scored 15 of his 25 points for Minnesota in the first quarter, before fouling out in frustration and being forced to watch the Timberwolves hang on for a 96-89 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Minnesota Timberwolves vs. New Orleans Pelicans

Items.description: — Khris Middleton scored 28 points, Giannis Antetokounmpo added 21 and the Milwaukee Bucks held on to beat the San Antonio Spurs 121-111 on Saturday night.
Items.vs: San Antonio Spurs vs. Milwaukee Bucks

Items.description: — Trail Blazers head coach Chauncey Billups was happy to have an extra pair of clothes on Saturday night. He needed them after getting drenched by his players as they celebrated his first career victory as a head coach.
Items.vs: Portland Trail Blazers vs. Phoenix Suns

Items.description: — Ja Morant led five starters in double figures with 28 points and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 120-114 in their home opener Saturday night.
— LaMelo Ball had a good first three quarters in Brooklyn, then decided it was best if he watched the fourth.
— Seth Curry's start resembled some of his big brother's hottest streaks.
— Jayson Tatum had 31 points and nine rebounds and the Boston Celtics avoided their first 0-3 start since the 2013-14 season with a 107-97 win over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
— Terrence Ross scored all 22 of his points in the fourth quarter, and the Orlando Magic beat the New York Knicks 110-104 on Sunday night.
Items.vs: New York Knicks vs. Orlando Magic

Items.description: — Stephen Curry scored 27 points and became the first player in Warriors franchise history to reach 5,000 assists, helping Golden State improve to 3-0 with a 119-107 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Sunday night.
Items.vs: Sacramento Kings vs. Golden State Warriors

Items.description: — Carmelo Anthony got the game ball after the Los Angeles Lakers’ first victory of the season.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Memphis Grizzlies

Items.description: — Jayson Tatum scored a season-high 41 points, Jaylen Brown added 30, including an emphatic dunk in overtime, and the Boston Celtics beat Charlotte 140-129 on Monday night, handing the Hornets their first loss of the season.
— Giannis Antetokounmpo went into attack mode with the defending NBA champion Milwaukee Bucks playing short-handed Monday night.
— Jimmy Butler kept getting to the rim, and predictably, scoring suddenly became pretty easy.

— Kevin Durant scored 25 points and the Brooklyn Nets bounced back from a poor finish a day earlier with a blistering start that sent them to a 104-90 victory over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
— Trae Young had 32 points and nine assists, John Collins scored 22 and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Detroit Pistons 122-104 on Monday night.
— DeMar DeRozan took control in the fourth quarter, something he's done plenty of times in Toronto.

— Brandon Ingram scored 27 points, Jonas Valanciunas had 22 points and a career-high 23 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped a season-opening three-game losing streak with a 107-98 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Monday night.

Items.description: — The tempers briefly flared between feisty guards Ricky Rubio and Facundo Campazzo as both got in each other's face late in the third quarter.
